However, year after year, the number of people living with HIV and AIDS in China has increased by 100,000.
Transmission of HIV through sex is an acute issue in the LGBT community in China.
Homosexuality was decriminalized in China in 1997, but is said to still dominate discrimination against LGBT people.
Because of the country's conservative values, studies have measured that 70-90% of men who have sex with other men will eventually marry women.
